details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: This desert heat is starting to get to me. I'm getting too old for this.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Orders said to get here as soon as possible. I wonder what this is all about?

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: So this is the outpost I'm supposed to command. Does not look like much.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Hello, private. I'm here to take command.

details.name: Guard
details.text: Sir! We've been expecting you. There is a message waiting for you.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Let's hear it then.

details.name: President Gideon
details.text: General Cyrus, I hope your trip went fine. Sorry for dispatching you on such a short notice, but the situation is getting out of hand and we need your experience.

details.name: President Gideon
details.text: You must have heard by now that a war broke out in the Amber Noon kingdom, with Ruby Dusk invading, and some of our forces got involved.

details.name: President Gideon
details.text: Warlord Grim of the Amber Noon contacted us, asking for help. Ruby Dusk attacked them without notice nor reason, driving their army deep into King Ludwig's domain.

details.name: President Gideon
details.text: Prince Tybalt is nowhere to be found. Warlord Grim asked us to intervene, and I agreed. It is a great opportunity to both weaken Ruby Dusk and get some favours from Amber Dusk, as Warlord Grim assured me, that King Ludwig is a generous man.

details.name: President Gideon
details.text: Or so it seemed... I have ordered Commando Blake to take a large chunk of our forces and deal with the invasion. It didn't work out so well. He tried to make a push towards Rubyport and failed.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: He did what? That's was so foolish of him.

details.name: President Gideon
details.text: This is where you come in. We still have to assist Amber Noon, and reinforce Blake. But before we can do this, we have to rebuild some of our forces. I assign that task to you. Commanding officer of the outpost knows the details.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: As usual, Blake rushed forward without much consideration, and now needs help.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Sir! I have a list of requirements for you, sent by president's advisor. Our forces here are lacking in all regards, I'm afraid.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Mechanised forces were taken by Blake on his initial expedition. Only bare minimum left.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Infantry has been reduced to only this guard unit, and another one up north, near damaged bridge. Reinforcing them will be our first objective.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: We have to recruit more infantry in the Barracks, so that we have at least 5 units in the field, including current ones.
Recruit Infantry units.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: I just noticed, that my active ability is not available. Looks like air support is lacking in this area.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: I still have my passive ability, and it should come in handy. It allows me to recruit Infantry and Mobile Infantry with less AP.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Resources are limited here, recruitment will take a couple of turns.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: New soldiers are ready and eager. We can move on to the next item on the list.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: We need at least three teams of Mobile Infantry. They are now available for recruitment in the Barracks.
Recruit Mobile Infantry units.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Another one done. These units should cover your scouting and support needs.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Only one more to go. Orders are to have at least two Tanks in the field. Factory is waiting for your request.
Deploy more Tanks.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: That should do it.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Do we have further instructions from high command?

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Yes Sir, we do. You are to take these newly formed forces and proceed to cross the border and provide assitance to any Amber Noon army you encounter.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Bridge over the river has been repaired and should be safe to use.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Send in a scouting party first. I have a bad feeling about this...

details.name: Scout
details.text: Roger.

details.name: Scout
details.text: Sir! We have reached the border tower, but it has Ruby Dusk colours! Ruby army is in the area.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Ruby Dusk is already here? They must be controlling Amber lands all the way to the capital. This complicates things.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Scout! Fall back before they spot you.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: I think we don't have a choice here. Let's take them head on.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: We should retake this tower and forward Barracks. It will reduce their already limited AP supply.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: Our main goal is to take the local HQ.
Capture the Ruby Dusk HQ.
General Cyrus must survive.

details.name: Sergeant
details.text: Objective captured, Sir.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: All units! Regroup at the captured HQ. We will proceed along that road as soon as possible.

details.name: General Cyrus
details.text: I have made a tactical mistake! Fall back!
